physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Generalized periareolar erythema, dimpling, firmness, and fixation in the central breast and right upper outer quadrant. Conspicuous breast nipple retraction compared to prior examinations. A 1-cm periareolar ulcerating skin plaque. Lumpectomy bed seroma palpable; no axillary adenopathy.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: More noticeable nipple retraction compared to previous examinations.
